query.result:
52 With the middle feet he bound the belly
53 and with the anterior ones he seized the arms;
54 then he bit him on one cheek and the other;

55 the direct ones he extended to the thighs,
56 and he put the tail between both of them
57 and behind, through the kidneys, he drew it up.

73 They made two arms of four hands;
74 the thighs with the legs and the belly and the chest
75 became limbs that were never seen.

76 Every first appearance there was hollow;
77 two and no one the perverse image
78 seemed; and thus they went with slow step.

79 As the lizard under the great heat 80 of the dog days, changing its skin, 81 lightning seems to cross the way,
82 thus seemed, coming towards the eyes 83 of the other two, a small serpent inflamed, 84 livid and black like large peppercorns;
85 and that part where first is taken 86 our nourishment, pierced one of them; 87 then it fell down before him stretched out.

88 The pierced one looked at it, but said nothing;
89 indeed, with his feet fixed, he yawned
90 as if sleep or fever assailed him.

91 He was looking at the serpent and at him;
92 one through the wound and the other through the mouth
93 were smoking strongly, and the smoke collided.

